The chunk defines two helper functions within `createLinearForceWidgets`, a method of a UI builder class for physics forces in Panda3D. The first function, `setAmplitude`, sets the amplitude of a linear force, while the second function, `toggleMassDependent`, toggles whether the force's effect depends on the mass of the object being acted upon. This code is part of creating widgets to control properties of linear forces in a physics simulation.

def createLinearForceWidgets(self, frame, pageName, forceName, force):
        def setAmplitude(amp, f = force):
            f.setAmplitude(amp)

        def toggleMassDependent(s=self, f=force, p=pageName, n=forceName):
            v = s.getVariable(p, n+' Mass Dependent')
            f.setMassDependent(v.get())
